
@startuml
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam noteBackgroundColor yellow

class House {
  - String address
  - String buildingMaterial
  - Basement basement
  - Set<Company> companies
  - Set<JobLog> jobLogs
}

class Basement {
  - String name
  - int size
  - String type
  - if (type == "earth") then
    - int humidityLevel
  endif
}

class Company {
  - String name
  - String address
  - Set<JobLog> jobLogs
}

class JobLog {
  - int hours
  - double price
  - House house
  - Company company
}

class SemiDetachedHouse {
  - boolean hasOwnGarden
  - int numberOfWindows
  - CarportOrGarage carportOrGarage
}

class CarportOrGarage {
  - boolean isDoubleCarport
  - boolean hasFlatRoof
  - boolean hasAutomaticGarageDoor
}

note right of House: A House can be a SemiDetachedHouse
note right of SemiDetachedHouse: Must have either CarportOrGarage (with Carport details) or Garage (with Garage details)

House --> Basement
House --> Company
House --> JobLog
House <|-- SemiDetachedHouse

SemiDetachedHouse --> CarportOrGarage

CarportOrGarage --> Carport
CarportOrGarage --> Garage

class Carport {
  - boolean isDoubleCarport
  - boolean hasFlatRoof
}

class Garage {
  - boolean hasAutomaticGarageDoor
}

CarportOrGarage <|-- Carport
CarportOrGarage <|-- Garage

@enduml

### Explanation:
- **House**: Base class with common attributes and relationships.
- **Company**: Services houses and records jobs.
- **JobLog**: Records job details for a company and house.
- **SemiDetachedHouse**: Specialization of `House` with additional attributes.
- **CarportOrGarage**: Abstract class that represents either a carport or a garage. It's used to differentiate between the two options in a semi-detached house.

